{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":856,"text":"I am in search of another planet\nin the universe where life exists."},{"time":6426,"text":"I can't see this planet\nwith my naked eyes"},{"time":9412,"text":"or even with the most powerful telescopes"},{"time":11722,"text":"we currently possess."},{"time":13787,"text":"But I know that it's there."},{"time":15875,"text":"And understanding contradictions\nthat occur in nature"},{"time":19042,"text":"will help us find it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21379,"text":"On our planet,"},{"time":22554,"text":"where there's water, there's life."},{"time":24892,"text":"So we look for planets that orbit\nat just the right distance"},{"time":27850,"text":"from their stars."},{"time":30418,"text":"At this distance,"},{"time":31593,"text":"shown in blue on this diagram\nfor stars of different temperatures,"},{"time":35097,"text":"planets could be warm enough\nfor water to flow on their surfaces"},{"time":38975,"text":"as lakes and oceans"},{"time":40397,"text":"where life might reside."},{"time":42787,"text":"Some astronomers focus their time\nand energy on finding planets"},{"time":46525,"text":"at these distances from their stars."},{"time":48990,"text":"What I do picks up where their job ends."},{"time":51869,"text":"I model the possible\nclimates of exoplanets."},{"time":55353,"text":"And here's why that's important:"},{"time":57203,"text":"there are many factors\nbesides distance from its star"},{"time":60717,"text":"that control whether\na planet can support life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64297,"text":"Take the planet Venus."},{"time":66646,"text":"It's named after the Roman goddess\nof love and beauty,"},{"time":70361,"text":"because of its benign,\nethereal appearance in the sky."},{"time":74487,"text":"But spacecraft measurements\nrevealed a different story."},{"time":78080,"text":"The surface temperature is close\nto 900 degrees Fahrenheit,"},{"time":82073,"text":"500 Celsius."},{"time":84151,"text":"That's hot enough to melt lead."},{"time":87115,"text":"Its thick atmosphere, not its distance\nfrom the sun, is the reason."},{"time":90977,"text":"It causes a greenhouse effect on steroids,"},{"time":94104,"text":"trapping heat from the sun\nand scorching the planet's surface."},{"time":98181,"text":"The reality totally contradicted\ninitial perceptions of this planet."},{"time":103728,"text":"From these lessons\nfrom our own solar system,"},{"time":106373,"text":"we've learned that a planet's atmosphere"},{"time":108413,"text":"is crucial to its climate\nand potential to host life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112967,"text":"We don't know what the atmospheres\nof these planets are like"},{"time":115906,"text":"because the planets are so small\nand dim compared to their stars"},{"time":120298,"text":"and so far away from us."},{"time":122500,"text":"For example, one of the closest planets\nthat could support surface water --"},{"time":126815,"text":"it's called Gliese 667 Cc --"},{"time":130196,"text":"such a glamorous name, right,\nnice phone number for a name --"},{"time":134156,"text":"it's 23 light years away."},{"time":137091,"text":"So that's more than 100 trillion miles."},{"time":140686,"text":"Trying to measure\nthe atmospheric composition"},{"time":143023,"text":"of an exoplanet passing\nin front of its host star is hard."},{"time":147444,"text":"It's like trying to see a fruit fly"},{"time":149348,"text":"passing in front of a car's headlight."},{"time":152126,"text":"OK, now imagine that car\nis 100 trillion miles away,"},{"time":155849,"text":"and you want to know\nthe precise color of that fly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160618,"text":"So I use computer models"},{"time":162399,"text":"to calculate the kind of atmosphere\na planet would need"},{"time":165526,"text":"to have a suitable climate\nfor water and life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169439,"text":"Here's an artist's concept\nof the planet Kepler-62f,"},{"time":173575,"text":"with the Earth for reference."},{"time":175507,"text":"It's 1,200 light years away,"},{"time":177571,"text":"and just 40 percent larger than Earth."},{"time":180313,"text":"Our NSF-funded work found that it\ncould be warm enough for open water"},{"time":184385,"text":"from many types of atmospheres\nand orientations of its orbit."},{"time":188518,"text":"So I'd like future telescopes\nto follow up on this planet"},{"time":191675,"text":"to look for signs of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194476,"text":"Ice on a planet's surface\nis also important for climate."},{"time":197889,"text":"Ice absorbs longer,\nredder wavelengths of light,"},{"time":201108,"text":"and reflects shorter, bluer light."},{"time":203870,"text":"That's why the iceberg\nin this photo looks so blue."},{"time":207092,"text":"The redder light from the sun\nis absorbed on its way through the ice."},{"time":210613,"text":"Only the blue light\nmakes it all the way to the bottom."},{"time":213947,"text":"Then it gets reflected\nback to up to our eyes"},{"time":216363,"text":"and we see blue ice."},{"time":218590,"text":"My models show that planets\norbiting cooler stars"},{"time":221588,"text":"could actually be warmer\nthan planets orbiting hotter stars."},{"time":224780,"text":"There's another contradiction --"},{"time":226343,"text":"that ice absorbs the longer\nwavelength light from cooler stars,"},{"time":230141,"text":"and that light, that energy,\nheats the ice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234622,"text":"Using climate models to explore"},{"time":237006,"text":"how these contradictions\ncan affect planetary climate"},{"time":240135,"text":"is vital to the search for life elsewhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244128,"text":"And it's no surprise\nthat this is my specialty."},{"time":247715,"text":"I'm an African-American female astronomer"},{"time":250524,"text":"and a classically trained actor"},{"time":252660,"text":"who loves to wear makeup\nand read fashion magazines,"},{"time":256519,"text":"so I am uniquely positioned to appreciate\ncontradictions in nature --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":261376,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":262512,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":266000,"text":"... and how they can inform our search\nfor the next planet where life exists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270645,"text":"My organization, Rising Stargirls,"},{"time":273177,"text":"teaches astronomy\nto middle-school girls of color,"},{"time":276629,"text":"using theater, writing and visual art."},{"time":280697,"text":"That's another contradiction --\nscience and art don't often go together,"},{"time":284698,"text":"but interweaving them can help\nthese girls bring their whole selves"},{"time":288524,"text":"to what they learn,"},{"time":289747,"text":"and maybe one day join\nthe ranks of astronomers"},{"time":293211,"text":"who are full of contradictions,"},{"time":294989,"text":"and use their backgrounds\nto discover, once and for all,"},{"time":298163,"text":"that we are truly not alone\nin the universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302433,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303608,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}